<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Flood in South Bangladesh Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed today
in south Bangladesh while the overall flood situation worsened
further following incessant rainfall along with on rush of hilly
water, according to official news agency Bangladesh Sangbad
Sangstha (BSS).
</P>
<P>
With the reports of ten fresh deaths, the death toll rose to 42
in the on-going flood, which has turned most parts of Bangladesh
as an inundated area, leaving millions of people homeless.
</P>
<P>
In Bandarban, one of the southern hill districts, nine people,
six of them belonging to one family, were killed today in a
landslide in Lama county.
</P>
<P>
The victim family was killed when a big chunk of mud collapsed
on their house while the three other people were killed in another
landslide in Kalagata hills, local police said.
</P>
<P>
The district administration said some 60,000 people were
affected and 2,000 thatched houses were damaged as heavy onrush of
water from the hills inundated six counties of Bandarban district.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, at least one person was killed, and an unspecified
number of people were injured in the flash flood which also caused
disruption of road communications at many places in Bangladesh's
largest port city of Chittagong.
</P>
<P>
According to an official handout, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina
today directed the armed forces to take all necessary steps to
tackle the current flood situation.
</P>
<P>
The army stationed in Chittagong has already sent 800 kilograms
of biscuits to Bandarban district as emergency relief from its own
resources while air force helicopters have also been operating
relief activities as road communication were disrupted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
