<HEADLINE> 19 People Feared Killed in Boat Capsize in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen people were feared drowned
today after a boat capsized in the river Sangu at Ruma county in
southern Bangladesh, said official news agency Bangladesh Sangbad
Sangstha (BSS).
</P>
<P>
Local police said the boat met with the accident at noon with
20 passengers on board.
</P>
<P>
The only passenger who survived the accident by swimming across
the river informed the police of the mishap and the police were
searching the bodies of the ill-fated passengers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
