<HEADLINE> Chinese University to Continue Assisting Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- China's Nanjing Agricultural
University has signed an accord with southwestern Kenya's Egerton
University, to continue assisting Egerton's training and research
in horticulture, the Kenyan News Agency (KNA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Japheth Kiptoon, Vice Chancellor of the Egerton University,
said at the signing ceremony at Egerton Friday that China has
donated equipment worth seven million Shillings (about 130,000
U.S. Dollars) to his university for training and research on
horticulture.
</P>
<P>
Two professors from the Nanjing Agricultural University have
worked in the horticultural department in Egerton University for
two years and are spoken highly of for their diligence and
fruitful researches.
</P>
<P>
Under the academic cooperation agreement, the Chinese
university will further help train staff in Egerton University
whose four lecturers will get China's scholarships for
postgraduate training.
</P>
<P>
Zhai Hugu, who signed the agreement on behalf of the Nanjing
Agricultural University, said his university will continue to
collaborate with Egerton University in training and research.
</P>
</TEXT>
