<HEADLINE> Russian, Finnish Presidents Hold Informal Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin had
informal talks with Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari on
Saturday in Karelia adjacent to Finland, where Yeltsin is having a
holiday.
</P>
<P>
Ahtisaari comes at the Russian president's invitation to spend
the weekend together, combining recreation with discussion of
bilateral and international matters.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish president intimated that the results of the NATO
Madrid summit would be one of the subjects during the two-day
talks with Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Ahtisaari said Russian-Finnish relations were in good shape,
which allowed the discussion of even serious issues in an informal
setting.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said he would suggest to Ahtisaari that joint border
control be organized and bilateral cooperation be enhanced in the
political, economic and other areas. 
</P>
