<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Link All Universities With Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is planning to link all its
universities to the Internet worldwide web site, the official
News Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
Dennis Onyekwelu, director of the Data Management Department
of the Nigerian Universities Commission said in Abuja today that
the plan has reached an advanced stage.
</P>
<P>
He said the plan is in line with the commission's objective of
developing and standardizing the information management base of
Nigerian universities.
</P>
<P>
The university Internet program is being undertaken by the
Abuja Internet Group, a non-governmental organization devoted to
connecting Nigeria with Internet.
</P>
<P>
Some Nigerian universities are already using E-mail services
but they have problems with the local telecommunications
services, which remain to be improved, Onyekwelu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
