<HEADLINE> EC Renews Commitment to Integrate Environment Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission has
adopted measures to improve and reinforce its internal procedures
to ensure a better integration of environmental consideration in
its policy-making and management.
</P>
<P>
The European Union's executive body said Friday that it was
keen to see the integration of environmental considerations in key
policy areas continued and strengthened, where substantial
progress has been made during the last couple of years.
</P>
<P>
The measures proposed include such as appraisals of the
environmental effects of new EC proposals, appointment of
environmental integration correspondents in each
Directorate-General and analysis of the environmental effects of
EU funding.
</P>
<P>
With this initiative, the EC has made a renewed political
commitment towards environmental considerations by reinforcing
existing measures and introducing new ones, recognizing the
important role it has to play in giving a lead and setting an
example within the EU decision-making process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
