<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Defense Minister Says Return to Army Draft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- French Defense Minister Alain
Richard said today that the French nation should retain the right
of returning to army draft, and said that he would propose to
parliament a new bill on the reform of army.
</P>
<P>
"Without idealizing what was the former military service, one
should breathe the spirit of defense in a democratic country which
is not subjected to an immediate threat, but is concerned about
its international responsibilities," said Richard in a speech to
members of a military academy in Cergy-Pontoise northwest of
Paris.
</P>
<P>
President Jacques Chirac decided in late 1995 to
professionalize the French army and stop the 200-year practice of
army draft in France.
</P>
<P>
Richard said that the "strategic data" which led France to
professionalize its army is not "eternal".
</P>
<P>
He also said that professionalization of the army is "a choice
not suffered by wanted" by France, which has seen the threat on
its European frontier "moving away but not inevitably
disappearing." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
