<DOCNO> XIE19970713.0023 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Routs Beijing to Remain Top in Chinese Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Hao Haidong scored a hat-trick to
inspire league leader Dalian Wanda to a 5-1 home victory over
Beijing Guo'an in China's professional soccer league in Dalian,
northeastern Liaoning province, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The win extended Dalian's unbeaten streak to 43 games in the
league since the 1995 season. The team now leads the league
standings with 25 points after nine games, 11 points ahead of
nearest contender Shanghai Shenhua.
</P>
<P>
Dalian led the first half 1-0 through Wang Tao, who blasted a
volley from in the box in the 15th minute. Beijing goalkeeper Fu
Bin touched the ball but failed to stop it from dashing into the
net.
</P>
<P>
The visitors' defence was falling apart in the second half
under the relentless attacks from the Dalian strikers, giving Hao
the playmaking chances before the home crowd.
</P>
<P>
Hao netted his first in the 67th minute before the visitors
scored their only goal four minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the last 18 minutes, Wang Peng scored one goal to bring
Dalian to a 3-1 lead and Hao scored another two to complete the
mauling.
</P>
<P>
In Jinan, Jinan Taishan beat August First 1-0 on a second-half
goal from Shao Yanjie, who converted a heading pass from Su
Maozhen in the 70th minute.
</P>
<P>
In Guangzhou, Guangdong Hongyuan became the only home team that
suffered a loss on Sunday when it was handed a 2-3 defeat by
visiting Vanguard Huandao.
</P>
<P>
Hongyuan now finished bottom in the league with only five
points.
</P>
<P>
All the other matches ended in draws. Tianjin Samsung tied
Sichuan Quanxing 1-1 in Tianjin, Qingdao Hainiu forced a goalless
home draw with Yanbian Aodong, while Shanghai Shenhua tied 0-0
with Guangzhou Apollo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
