<HEADLINE> Monsoon Still Active Over Flood-hit Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The overall flood situation in
Bangladesh remains unchanged today as the monsoon is still very
active with light to heavy rainfalls recorded at most places.
</P>
<P>
According to the Flood Information Center, the major rivers in
the Meghna basin today recorded rises at most points and are
flowing above danger levels.
</P>
<P>
In the Brahmaputra basin, the Brahmaputra is flowing 27 cm
above the danger mark at Bahadurabad town. All the rivers in the
basin have registered rises at all points but are still flowing
below danger marks, the information center said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that all the rivers in the Ganges basin registered
rises at all points but are flowing below danger marks.
</P>
<P>
However, according to the information center, as many as 11
rivers of the country's three major basins are still flowing above
danger levels.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an inter-ministerial disaster management committee
today discussed the damage brought about by the sudden flood,
which has caused at least 57 people dead and millions of people
homeless since July 8.
</P>
<P>
The committee also held detailed discussions on what measures
could be undertaken to face the deluge as well as to repair the
damage caused by the floods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
