<HEADLINE> Participation of Women in Development Ensured: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister Lokendra
Bahadur Chand said here today that the government is committed to
ensuring maximum participation of women in the mainstream of
national development.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a seminar on gender perspectives in development,
Chand said the government has required that at least 20 percent of
women representatives get represented in the local bodies.
</P>
<P>
And an ordinance for women development has been promulgated to
give a concrete shape to Nepal's commitments in this regard, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said women make up half of the country's
population, but are found to be lagging behind men in education,
health, politics and social affairs.
</P>
<P>
Realizing that no development program can be successful without
women's participation, the government is striving to reduce this
gender gap, he said.  
