<HEADLINE> Ceremony Honors Donations for Tibetan Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held in the capital
of the Tibet Autonomous Region today at which some 30 Chinese
publishing houses donated 435,000 yuan (about 50,000 US dollars)
to publish books for Tibetan children, both in Chinese and Tibetan.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the program, which is part of the "Tibet Project
Hope Library", is to record and develop Tibetan culture. The
program is backed up by the central government.
</P>
<P>
"Project Hope" is a nationwide charitable program. It started
in 1989 and is designed to help students in poverty-stricken
regions.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that the Tibet People's Publishing House will use
the money to collect and publish Tibetan folk literature in order
to conduct education in patriotism among 780,000 young Tibetans.
