<HEADLINE> German Auto-Maker Donates Car And Parts To China For Teaching Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Audi, a subsidiary of
Volkswagen AG, recently donated an automobile and engine that can
be disassembled for teaching purposes to the Automotive
Engineering Department of China's Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior executive, they are an entire automobile
and a four-cylinder, 113-horsepower engine.
</P>
<P>
Audi increased its ties with Chinese institutes of higher
learning earlier this year, and Qinghua was one of the first to
benefit, the executive said.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua is one of China's elite universities, and has China's
largest automotive engineering department.
</P>
<P>
Audis have been built and marketed under license in China by
the First Auto Works Group since 1988. The Germans plan to further
tap the China market in the future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
