<HEADLINE> Improving Efficiency in Agricultural Production Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-premier Jiang
Chunyun, during a recent inspection tour of northwest China's
Gansu province, stressed the importance of using scientific
methods in agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
He noted that although the province is basically
self-sufficient in grain and the number of poor people there is
decreasing, improving efficiency in agriculture is still a major
task.
</P>
<P>
He commented on continuing the land contract-system and easing
the burdens on farmers. The shortage of water remains one of the
major factors holding back the agricultural development in the
province, he said, adding that more attention should be given to
infrastructure for saving water and for irrigation.
</P>
<P>
To save more water, environmental protection work must be
improved and more trees planted, Jiang said. He went on to say
that the strategy of improving agriculture by relying on science
and education must be carried out in an effective way. "The
emphasis should be given to agricultural science and technology,
which are the main productive forces," he explained.
</P>
<P>
He also emphasized the importance of combining commerce,
industry, and agriculture, as an effective way to help farmers
enter the market and improve agricultural efficiency.  
</P>
</TEXT>
