this year, she said, hence there was room for the improvement of
the workers' salaries and working condition.
</P>
<P>
Wages had been increased over the past fews years, but they
failed to keep pace with inflation, she said.
</P>
<P>
Chitauro stressed the need to maintain positive labor
relations "for the benefit of both the employer and the worker
and the national economy."  
</P>
