<HEADLINE> Chinese Female Lifters Dominate Asian Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGZHOU, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Female weightlifters made
another clean sweep of gold medals in all the events they
participated in at the 10th Asian Women's Weightlifting
Championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Compared to their male counterparts, the Chinese female lifters
nearly broke all the world records of the events they took part in
since the championships began here on July 5.
</P>
<P>
Gao Shihong of China nearly broke the world record of the 70-kg
total as she garnered 227.5 kilograms. The world record is 230-kg.
</P>
<P>
But Gao did broke snatch world mark with a successful attempt
at 103.5 kilograms. Her compatriot Qu Lihua claimed the other
world record as she lifted 130-kg in the clean and jerk.
</P>
<P>
Qu Lihua finished second overall with a total of 220-kg,
followed by Kuo Shu-Feng of Chinese Taipei in the third place at
217.5-kg.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese lifters skipped the women's 76-kg category and Ok
Son-Hua of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea took all the
gold of the three events in the class.
</P>
<P>
Ok Son-Hui first brought home the gold of the snatch with a
lift of 97.5-kg. She went on to pick up the title of the clean and
jerk in a weight of 120-kg. That also gave her a winning total of
217.5-kg.
</P>
<P>
Huang Si-li of Chinese Taipei took the silver in the snatch
with 95-kg, followed by Sumita Laha of India in the third place at
92.5-kg.
</P>
<P>
But Huang Si-li faded in the clean and jerk and Sumita Laha
took the chance to capture the silver with a lift of 117.5-kg,
Kumi Haseba of Japan came third at 112.5-kg.
</P>
<P>
Kumi Haeseba also claimed the bronze medal in the total with
205 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 91-kg class, Wang Baofu of China clinched the gold
in the snatch with a lift of 170-kg. He was followed by Alexey
Chouikov of Kazakhastan in the second place at 160-kg. Another
lifter from Kazakhastan was third with 152.5-kg.
</P>
<P>
The clean and jerk title went to Chun Yong-Sung of South Korea
who lifted 202.5-kg. But Wang Baofu still secured his total title
with 362.5-kg.
</P>
<P>
The men's class was dominated by Khrapatyy of Kazakhastan who
bagged all the three gold medals on offer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
