<HEADLINE> Shanghai Developing New Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- New product development has
become a new trend fuelling the speedy economic growth in this,
China's economic powerhouse.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai plans to generate new industrial products worth 85
billion yuan in output value this year, a 20 percent rise over
last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
The city began its new-product development project in 1989, and
poured 7.9 billion yuan into it during the 1991-1995 period,
adding more than 33 billion yuan in output value and 6.4 billion
yuan in profits over the five years.
</P>
<P>
In addition to financial support, Shanghai has issued a series
of favorable policies to encourage the development and application
of new technology. This has given new impetus to local industrial
development by further improving the restructuring of the city's
product mix.
</P>
<P>
This year priority will be given to the development of ten
products which sell well: motorcycles, elevators, escalators,
refrigerators, washing machines, garments, microwave ovens,
foodstuffs, air-conditioners and chemicals for daily use.
</P>
<P>
During the 1996-2000 period the city plans to establish ten
pilot enterprises for technological improvement and designate 100
undertakings to set up technology centers in a bid to carry out
100 major projects in the sector and develop a group of
high-value-added and hi-tech products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
