<HEADLINE> PLC Member Deems HK's Image Abroad Top Priority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Newly-elected Provisional
Legislative Council (PLC) member Choy So-yuk places strengthening
Hong Kong's international image as one of her top missions in the
Hong Kong legislature.
</P>
<P>
Filling the seat vacated by Maria Tam Wai-chu, the 47-year-old
Choy told the Hong Kong Standard newspaper that she aims to uphold
Hong Kong's transition and the implementation of "one country,
two systems."
</P>
<P>
"Our work has just started," she said, adding: "I am doing what
every Hong Kong person can and should do."
</P>
<P>
Choy is especially interested in strengthening Hong Kong's
image abroad, according to the Hong Kong Standard today.
</P>
<P>
A favorable image will attract foreign investment and retain
Hong Kong's global status, the paper quoted her as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Having conducted business overseas and traveled worldwide, I
found many people's perceptions about Hong Kong are very much
affected by media reports," Choy said.
</P>
<P>
"They have created a misconception about Hong Kong," she went
on to say. "For example, a friend of mine in Germany thinks no
demonstrations or petitions will be allowed here" after the July 1
handover.
</P>
<P>
Choy, a business executive and a member of the central
committee of the Hong Kong Progressive Alliance, was elected to
the PLC on July 8.  
</P>
