<HEADLINE> 1999 SEA Games May Be delayed, Official Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The 1999 Southeast Asian
Games might be delayed due to the expanding events and rising
costs, a Malaysian sports official said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 games are to be held in Jakarta, Indonesia, and Kuala
Lumpur will stage the 1999 games. But the Malaysian capital, busy
preparing to stage the 1998 Commonwealth Games, is not keen to act
as host for the 1999 competition.
</P>
<P>
Sieh Kok Chi, secretary of the Olympic Council of Malaysia,
said another Malaysian city might be persuaded to act as host,
according to the national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
"Maybe the games should take a rest in 1999. Then the member
countries can reassess the objective and its achievement and
decide whether they want it to continue." he added.
</P>
<P>
Sieh suggested cutting costs by using university hostels rather
than hotels to house athletes and officials, reducing the number
of events and the duration of the games.
</P>
<P>
Countries and regions take part in the SEA Games are Malaysia,
Indonesia, Singapore, Thailand, the Philippines, Laos, Cambodia,
Burma, Vietnam and Brunei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
