<DOCNO> XIE19970713.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian HIV Carriers Increase Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 13 (Xinhua) -- An average of 100 more people
contract HIV virus that causes the deadly disease of AIDS each day
in Russia, bringing the country to the verge of the most dangerous
situation of epidemic diseases in a century, Russian News reported.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper reported after making an interview with the
country's AIDS expert and head of Russia's AIDS center, Vadim
Pokrovskij.
</P>
<P>
Pokrovskij reviewed the spread of HIV virus in the country,
saying the sharp increase of HIV carriers in Russia began in
January 1987.
</P>
<P>
The Russian AIDS center now has recorded 4,830 cases of
HIV-positives, among which 259 were AIDS-infected including 103
children. By now 239 of the 259 AIDS sufferers have died.
</P>
<P>
Drug addicts are the most vulnerable group in Russia. Each day,
the AIDS center will add 10 to 12 more drug addicts carrying HIV,
Pokrovskij said.
</P>
<P>
He also predicted that a peak period of HIV proliferation will
occur between late 1997 and early 1998 in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Though the virus' spreading may slow down after this period, he
said, some 100,000 to 200,000 more people will become HIV-positive
each year.
</P>
<P>
The expert called on the media, the medical and educational
departments to give more publicity to the danger of AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Since it is unlikely to find an effective way to cure AIDS
disease in the coming years, the adoption of more precautious
measures will be the only way to prevent further spread of any
possible disasters, Pokrovskij added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970713.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
