<HEADLINE> India to Hold Presidential Election Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Polling for the 11th
presidential election will be held across India tomorrow with
incumbent Vice-President Kocheril Raman Narayanan's victory a
foregone conclusion, the Press Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
Though India's former Chief Election Commissioner T. N. Seshan
is in the fray with the support of a regional party, Narayanan is
likely to have smooth sailing as his candidature is being
supported by the ruling United Front, the Congress Party and the
Bharatiya Janata Party, among others.
</P>
<P>
After scrutiny of nominations on June 24, only those of
Narayanan and Seshan were accepted as valid.
</P>
<P>
Because Seshan refuses to withdraw from the race, a polling
will have to be held as scheduled on July 14.
</P>
<P>
However, Narayanan is believed to enjoy the support of more
than 80 percent of this year's 4,848-strong Electoral College
which comprises members of parliament and state legislative
assemblies in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to an Election Commission spokesman, polling will be
held between 10:00 and 17:00 hours local time at the Parliament
House in the capital and polling stations across the country.
</P>
<P>
Ballot boxes and ballot papers have been flown to all polling
stations under tight security and will be flown back to the
capital and stored in the Parliament House till July 17.
</P>
<P>
The five-year tenure of President Shanker Dayal Sharma expires
on July 24. The new president to be elected is expected to take
the oath of office the next day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
