<HEADLINE> 13 Tanzanians Killed by Lions in Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen Tanzanian
villagers have been killed and seven others wounded by man-eater
lions in the last six months.
</P>
<P>
The local paper "Guardian" quoted Tanzanian Minister for
Natural Resources and Tourism Zakia Meghji over the weekend as
saying that villagers in Mkuranga District, south of Dar es
Salaam, are living in terror of the lions.
</P>
<P>
There are reports saying that the lions are still being seen
in some Mkuranga villages, he said, noting that "efforts will be
mounted to have them killed to restore peace in the area."
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains are believed to have forced the lion population to
migrate closer to human settlements in Mkuranga District, which
borders Selous Game Reserve covering 54,390 square kilometers,
said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
