<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe has won a lucrative
contract to export small arms ammunition, uniforms, boots and dry
food rations to the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) worth
about 500,000 U.S. Dollars, the Sunday Mail reported today.
