The move came after weeks of violent demonstrations and
protests in the West Bank and Gaza Strip resulted from Jewish
settlement expansion. An anti-Islamic poster depicting Prophet
Muhammad as a pig set off a wave of violent clashes between
Palestinians and Israeli soldiers in Hebron.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army has arrested a number of Palestinian activists
allegedly responsible for resistance activities in Hebron. The
army has also decided to dispatch more undercover personnel to
infiltrate into Palestinian ranks to arrest more in the largely
self-rule city.
</P>
<P>
In addition, word has been spread that more sanctions against
the Palestinians would be forthcoming if violence continues.
</P>
<P>
Unidentified sources were quoted in the report as alleging
that Palestinian President Yasser Arafat has ordered continuous
violence in order to exert pressure on the hardline Israeli
government.
</P>
<P>
Arafat is leaving for a trip to Britain and Austria
Monday. Israel fears that uprising-type violence would escalate
in his absence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
