<HEADLINE> New Simsim Variety Developed in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan researchers have
developed a new simsim variety that will increase output twice,
local paper "The Monitor" said today.
</P>
<P>
Busolo Bulafu, a researcher of Agricultural Researcher Station
in Serere, said his colleagues have distributed the seeds of the
new variety, EM-14, to local farmers in Soroti District, east
Uganda for multiplication.
</P>
<P>
The new variety produces 900 kilograms a hectare, while the
other local varieties produce 300 kilograms under the same
condition, said the report quoting Busolo Bulafu.
</P>
<P>
The researchers of the station now are collecting data for
presentation to the Ministry of Agriculture for classification,
said the report.  
