<HEADLINE> Sino-US Cable Venture to Be Built in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States have
signed a contract to jointly build an electric cable plant in
eastern China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will be run by the Shandong Yanggu Electric
Cable Group Company and Pacific Shareholding Ltd, according to the
contract, signed during the ongoing '97 China Qingdao Foreign
Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture involves a total investment of 29 million US
dollars, with the Chinese and American sides investing 45 percent
and 55 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
During the contract period of 40 years the venture will produce
30,000 km of electric wires and cables each year. 
