<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Kill 41 Thais Daily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 13 (Xinhua) -- An average of 41 Thais die every
day from road accidents, caused mostly by drunken driving.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents are the main cause of deaths in the country,
according to Supakorn Buasai, a leading researcher at the Health
System Research Institute.
</P>
<P>
He put economic losses from road mishaps at 100 billion baht
(3.5 billion U.S. dollars) a year.
</P>
<P>
Road death tolls are 1.5 times higher than deaths caused by
heart diseases, five times higher than deaths caused by AIDS and
10 times higher than murder, according to the researcher.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
