<HEADLINE> Italy Urges for Resuming Middle East Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The stalemate in the Middle East
peace process would only bring about new conflicts and violence,
and efforts should be made to resume talks between Israel and
Palestine, Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said here today.
</P>
<P>
Dini made the remarks after coming back from the fifth
Mediterranean Forum held in Algiers, Algeria, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that the recent tense situation in
the Middle East, which was aggravated by Israel's construction of
a new Jewish settlement in Arab East Jerusalem earlier this year,
was disappointing.
</P>
<P>
He condemned Israel's settlement practice as a negative
practice which destroyed the atmosphere of peace talks, the only
way to help find a real resolution to the issue.
</P>
<P>
He added that peace in the Middle East was an essential
pre-condition for maintaining peace and stability in the
Mediterranean region.
</P>
<P>
Peace process in the Middle East was among one of the major
topics of the two-day Mediterranean Forum, which
gathered together foreign ministers from 11 Mediterranean basin
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
