<HEADLINE> Serbia's Foreign Trade Up in First Half of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Republic of Serbia of the
Yugoslav Federal Republic posted a total of 2.119 billion US
dollars in foreign trade in the first half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released today by the Serbian Economic Federation
show that its exports stood at 966 million dollars, increasing 27
over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Serbia's export products include pig iron, rolled steel,
beverage, tobacco, fruits, vegetables, organic chemical products,
raw plastics and clothing, and its main imports are oil, oil
products, natural gas, cotton yarn, cloth, textiles, ore, scrap
metals, paperboard, paper and grains.
</P>
<P>
Germany, Russia, Italy, the Republic of Srpska and Macedonia
are the main trade partners of Serbia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
