<HEADLINE> Floods Hit Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- At least one person and five
others disappeared -- four of them children -- in the flood caused
by pouring rains since Thursday night in northern Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The national press reported that the floods hit six
municipalities of the Valles del Tuy, in the state of Miranda,
bringing down four bridges, as well as flooding the metropolitan
airport, and causing considerable damage to a passenger terminal
and some businesses.
</P>
<P>
More than one thousand houses were damaged, and some of them
were completely destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Rain fell all day on Friday, increasing the danger of more
floods, since many rivers threatened with outflowing.
</P>
<P>
All the roads suffered landslides, flooding, fallen trees,
cutting the communication with many towns and cities.
</P>
<P>
The firefighting brigade chief of Miranda state, Miguel
Castellanos, said that at least 450 firefighters joined the
rescue work and assisting the inhabitants of the six
municipalities of Tuy that suffered the biggest damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
