<HEADLINE> Bosnian Serb President Meets Krajisnik </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Bosnian Serb President Biljana
Plavsic today held a closed-door meeting with Momcilo Krajisnik,
the Serb member of Bosnia's three-member presidency, in her power
base, Banja Luka, said a report of the official Tanjug news agency.
</P>
<P>
This was the first meeting between the two Bosnian Serb
leaders, but they did not issue any formal statement after the
two-hour meeting.
</P>
<P>
Krajisnik only briefed the reporters that they were making some
progress during the talk that would continue tomorrow while
Plavsic remained silent.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held when Plavsic was battling Bosnian Serb
hard-liners who see her as too moderate. She has been the only
senior Serb official to advocate closer compliance with the Dayton
accords and has accused the hard-line leadership of corruption.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Serb parliament voted a law which it says
enabled it to strip her of her powers and transfer them to a
defense council. She says the vote was illegal because she had
dissolved the parliament a day earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
