<HEADLINE> Dagang Oilfield Produces 100 Million Tons In 33 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Dagang Oilfield, located
southeast of this largest port city in north China, has
produced a total of 100 million tons of crude oil since it began
prospecting 33 years ago.
</P>
<P>
It turned out more than 2.18 million tons of crude oil
and 193 million cu m of natural gas and verified 125 million tons
of oil reserve during the first half of this year, all surpassing
the targets set for this period.
</P>
<P>
The field began its prospecting in 1964 and has developed 21
oil and natural gas wells, forming an annual production capacity
of 4.3 million tons of crude oil and 360 million cu m of natural
gas. It also has a 2.5 million tons of crude-oil processing
capacity a year.
</P>
<P>
Dagang field, covering a prospecting area of 18,600 sq km in 25
districts, counties and cities, has now become a modern
comprehensive oil and natural gas base integrated with production,
processing, machine building, research and design. It ranked sixth
in the country with 4.34 million tons of crude oil output last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
