<HEADLINE> New Oil Well Starts Producing in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, July 12 (Xinhua) -- A new oil well in the northeast of
Ecuador started to produce 5,000 barrels of high quality crude a
day, said spokesmen of the state enterprise Petroproduction.
</P>
<P>
The well is located in the northeastern province of Sucumbios,
in a jungle zone bordering with Colombia, said the sources, quoted
today by the press.
</P>
<P>
Petroproduction operates 485 wells that produce 303,000 of oil
a day, almost 80 percent of the 375,000 barrels a day of the
national output.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador exports some 250,000 barrels a day, which finance 50
percent of the government budget. 
</P>
