<HEADLINE> Hingis Helps Switzerland into Fed Cup Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon champion Martina Hingis
made a rare home appearance on Saturday to help Switzerland into a
2-0 lead over Argentina in their Fed Cup World Group one play-off.
</P>
<P>
Patty Schnyder also won her singles to leave Switzerland
needing just one victory from Sunday's reverse singles and doubles
to reach the top group next year.
</P>
<P>
Only about 1,000 spectators watched the 16-year-old Swiss
heroine killing off Maria Jose Gaidano 6-1 6-2 in just 49 minutes.
</P>
<P>
While Hingis eased into the competition, Schnyder had a harder
time to face Argentina's top ranked player, number 37 Florencia
Labat before finally triumphing 3-6, 7-5, 10-8 in two hours 26
minutes. 
</P>
