<HEADLINE> Zambia Qualify for African Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Zambia became the first
African Nations Cup qualifiers after defeating Malawi 3-1 at
Independence Stadium in Lusaka, South Africa, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The convincing win moved Zambia to 11 points in Group 7,
leaving Malawi and Mozambique to fight for the second qualifying
spot.
</P>
<P>
Namibia fell 1-0 at home to Cameroon, and the result leaves
Cameroon needing one point from their final Group 5 fixture
against Kenya to qualify, while Namibia must collect at least one
point in Gabon to fill the other slot.
</P>
<P>
An early goal from Abdelkarim Kherris gave Algeria a 1-0 home
victory over Mali and kept alive their hopes of being among the 16
challengers for the title held by South Africa. 
</P>
