<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech President to Run for Second Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Czech President Vaclav Havel said
today he would run for his second term in the presidential
elections scheduled for early 1998.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Vaclav Claus, also president of the Civic
Democratic Party which is the largest ruling party in the country,
welcomed Havel's decision, saying that his party would fully
support Havel in his running.
</P>
<P>
Local observers said that nobody so far can replace Havel in
the Czech political life, who was elected President of the Czech
Republic in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Under the Czech constitution, the president can run only two
consecutive terms. If elected, Havel will serve his last five-year
term. 
</P>
</TEXT>
